<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7703> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7703" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Leg., lieut. of L. Antonius, 41, of Sex. Pompey, 40-36 (see MRR 2.376, 405). Wiseman (CR 15, 1965, 19-20, and NM 266, no. 434) suggests that his name should be read as [Ti]tisienus Gallus.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6394> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6394" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "An officer (#, App. BC 5.104) in command of land forces under Sextus Pompey, who fought against Lepidus (App. BC 5.104; Dio 49.8), then came to Messana (App. BC 5.117; Dio 49.8; Zonar. 10.25), and surrendered after Naulochus (App. BC 5.121; Dio 49.10-11; Zonar. 10.25)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6252> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6252" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. An officer under Lucius Anto nius, who drove Octavian back from Nursia (Dio 48.13.2), and was sent with 4000 horse to harry his communications during the siege of Perusia (App. BC 5.32)." .
